    <body><div type="letter">
      <p>6 o'clock. Mondy afternoon</p>
      <p>Dearest L--</p>
      <p>I hope you &amp; Byron have recd my 2 letters by this day's post.</p>
      <p>I have had today the severest possible pain,-- which has quite appalled everyone,</p>
      <p>(my Mother, Mr Philips &amp;c). With the utmost difficulty we have moderated it; by means of opium,-- Esher [double underline. Dr West came in the middle of it luckily, &amp; I am now much better. I am certainly stronger at presents, but as to pain far worse than of late. This</p>
      <p>[text on page 3 is written sideways on the page]</p>
      <p>is curious. Dr West is most attentive &amp; excellent, &amp; desires to be sent to even in the night. He says these frightful pains must be stopped.</p>
      <p>All Well, in all other aspects. Love to Byron, &amp; tell him I have been suffering somewhat.</p>
    </div></body>
